==English==
===Etymology===
[[Retronym]] for '''television''', coined after the invention of [[colour television]] to refer specifically to the type of television existing before then.
[[Category:Retronyms]]

===Noun===
'''[[black-and-white]] [[television]]''' (''[[countable]] and [[uncountable]]; plural'' '''black-and-white televisions''')

#A [[monochrome]] system of transmitting and receiving television signals.
#A [[television set]] that displays only monochrome images.

====Antonyms====
*(''system''): [[color television]], [[colour television]]
*(''television set''): color television, colour television